Tabela exemplo 1:

   A B C y
e1 1 1 1 1
e2 0 0 1 0
e3 1 0 1 0

Número de regras = 2

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

1) Garante que pelo menos uma feature esteja em uma regra

(¬s1,A V ¬s1,B V ¬s1,C)
(¬s2,A V ¬s2,B V ¬s2,C)

2) Define a variável dº que rejeita as linhas com a feature
sendo 0 e o d¹ com as features sendo 1

(¬dº1,A V ¬s1,A)
(¬dº1,A V l1,A)
(s1,A V ¬l1,A V dº1,A)
(¬dº1,B V ¬s1,B)
(¬dº1,B V l1,B)
(s1,B V ¬l1,B V dº1,B)
(¬dº1,C V ¬s1,C)
(¬dº1,C V l1,C)
(s1,C V ¬l1,C V dº1,C)

(¬dº2,A V ¬s2,A)
(¬dº2,A V l2,A)
(s2,A V ¬l2,A V dº2,A)
(¬dº2,B V ¬s2,B)
(¬dº2,B V l2,B)
(s2,B V ¬l2,B V dº2,B)
(¬dº2,C V ¬s2,C)
(¬dº2,C V l2,C)
(s2,C V ¬l2,C V dº2,C)

(¬d¹1,A V ¬s1,A)
(¬d¹1,A V ¬l1,A)
(s1,A V l1,A V d¹1,A)
(¬d¹1,B V ¬s1,B)
(¬d¹1,B V ¬l1,B)
(s1,B V l1,B V d¹1,B)
(¬d¹1,C V ¬s1,C)
(¬d¹1,C V ¬l1,C)
(s1,C V l1,C V d¹1,C)

(¬d¹2,A V ¬s2,A)
(¬d¹2,A V ¬l2,A)
(s2,A V l2,A V d¹2,A)
(¬d¹2,B V ¬s2,B)
(¬d¹2,B V ¬l2,B)
(s2,B V l2,B V d¹2,B)
(¬d¹2,C V ¬s2,C)
(¬d¹2,C V ¬l2,C)
(s2,C V l2,C V d¹2,C)

? l | 26 C

3) Força que todas as regras de todas as linhas, cujo y seja = 0,
sejam anuladas. E as que o y seja = 1, sejam positivadas

e1
c1 V (d¹1,A V d¹1,B V d¹1,C)
c2 V (d¹2,A V d¹2,B V d¹2,C)

e2
¬c1 V (dº1,A V dº1,B V d¹1,C)
¬c2 V (dº2,A V dº2,B V d¹2,C)

e3
¬c1 V (d¹1,A V dº1,B V d¹1,C)
¬c2 V (d¹2,A V dº2,B V d¹2,C)

? l | 32 C

4.1) Restrições que garantem que uma regra cobre algum exemplo seja com y = 0 ou y = 1

e2
cr1,e2 <-> (¬c1 ^ ¬dº1,A ^ ¬dº1,B ^ ¬d¹1,C)
cr2,e2 <-> (¬c2 ^ ¬dº2,A ^ ¬dº2,B ^ ¬d¹2,C)

e3
cr1,e3 <-> (¬c1 ^ ¬d¹1,A ^ ¬dº1,B ^ ¬d¹1,C)
cr2,e3 <-> (¬c2 ^ ¬d¹2,A ^ ¬dº2,B ^ ¬d¹2,C)

e1
cr1,e1 <-> (c1 ^ ¬d¹1,A ^ ¬d¹1,B ^ ¬d¹1,C)
cr2,e1 <-> (c2 ^ ¬d¹2,A ^ ¬d¹2,B ^ ¬d¹2,C)

Equivalencia:
e2
cr1,e2 -> (¬c1 ^ ¬dº1,A ^ ¬dº1,B ^ ¬d¹1,C) =
¬cr1,e2 V (¬c1 ^ ¬dº1,A ^ ¬dº1,B ^ ¬d¹1,C) =

- (¬cr1,e2 V ¬c1)
- (¬cr1,e2 V ¬dº1,A)
- (¬cr1,e2 V ¬dº1,B)
- (¬cr1,e2 V ¬d¹1,C)

cr1,e2 <- (¬c1 ^ ¬dº1,A ^ ¬dº1,B ^ ¬d¹1,C) =
cr1,e2 V ¬(¬c1 ^ ¬dº1,A ^ ¬dº1,B ^ ¬d¹1,C) =

- (cr1,e2 V c1 V dº1,A V dº1,B V d¹1,C)

e3
cr1,e3 -> (¬c1 ^ ¬d¹1,A ^ ¬dº1,B ^ ¬d¹1,C) =
¬cr1,e3 V (¬c1 ^ ¬d¹1,A ^ ¬dº1,B ^ ¬d¹1,C) =

- (¬cr1,e3 V ¬c1)
- (¬cr1,e3 V ¬d¹1,A)
- (¬cr1,e3 V ¬dº1,B)
- (¬cr1,e3 V ¬d¹1,C)

cr1,e3 <- (¬c1 ^ ¬d¹1,A ^ ¬dº1,B ^ ¬d¹1,C) =
cr1,e3 V ¬(¬c1 ^ ¬d¹1,A ^ ¬dº1,B ^ ¬d¹1,C) =

- (cr1,e3 V c1 V d¹1,A V dº1,B V d¹1,C)

e1
cr1,e1 -> (c1 ^ ¬d¹1,A ^ ¬d¹1,B ^ ¬d¹1,C) =
¬cr1,e1 V (c1 ^ ¬d¹1,A ^ ¬d¹1,B ^ ¬d¹1,C) =

- (¬cr1,e1 V c1)
- (¬cr1,e1 V ¬d¹1,A)
- (¬cr1,e1 V ¬d¹1,B)
- (¬cr1,e1 V ¬d¹1,C)

cr1,e1 <- (c1 ^ ¬d¹1,A ^ ¬d¹1,B ^ ¬d¹1,C) =
cr1,e1 V ¬(c1 ^ ¬d¹1,A ^ ¬d¹1,B ^ ¬d¹1,C) =

- (cr1,e1 V ¬c1 V d¹1,A V d¹1,B V d¹1,C)

Sendo assim, as novas cláusulas ficarão da seguinte maneira:
(¬cr1,e2 V ¬c1)
(¬cr1,e2 V ¬dº1,A)
(¬cr1,e2 V ¬dº1,B)
(¬cr1,e2 V ¬d¹1,C)
(cr1,e2 V c1 V dº1,A V dº1,B V d¹1,C)

(¬cr2,e2 V ¬c2)
(¬cr2,e2 V ¬dº2,A)
(¬cr2,e2 V ¬dº2,B)
(¬cr2,e2 V ¬d¹2,C)
(cr2,e2 V c2 V dº2,A V dº2,B V d¹2,C)

(¬cr1,e3 V ¬c1)
(¬cr1,e3 V ¬d¹1,A)
(¬cr1,e3 V ¬dº1,B)
(¬cr1,e3 V ¬d¹1,C)
(cr1,e3 V c1 V d¹1,A V dº1,B V d¹1,C)

(¬cr2,e3 V ¬c2)
(¬cr2,e3 V ¬d¹2,A)
(¬cr2,e3 V ¬dº2,B)
(¬cr2,e3 V ¬d¹2,C)
(cr2,e3 V c2 V d¹2,A V dº2,B V d¹2,C)

(¬cr1,e1 V c1)
(¬cr1,e1 V ¬d¹1,A)
(¬cr1,e1 V ¬d¹1,B)
(¬cr1,e1 V ¬d¹1,C)
(cr1,e1 V ¬c1 V d¹1,A V d¹1,B V d¹1,C)

(¬cr2,e1 V c2)
(¬cr2,e1 V ¬d¹2,A)
(¬cr2,e1 V ¬d¹2,B)
(¬cr2,e1 V ¬d¹2,C)
(cr2,e1 V ¬c2 V d¹2,A V d¹2,B V d¹2,C)

4.2) todos exemplo devem ser cobertos
(cr1,e1 V cr2,e1)
(cr1,e2 V cr2,e2)
(cr1,e3 V cr2,e3)

12 l | 59 C

5) restrição que evita dois termos iguais serem associados com classes distintas

(z1 V zA V zB V zC)

(¬z1 V ¬c1 V c2)
(¬z1 V c1 V ¬c2)

(¬zA V ¬s1,A)
(¬zA V ¬s2,A)
(¬zA V l1,A)
(¬zA V ¬l2,A)
(¬zA V ¬l1,A)
(¬zA V l2,A)

(¬zB V ¬s1,B)
(¬zB V ¬s2,B)
(¬zB V l1,B)
(¬zB V ¬l2,B)
(¬zB V ¬l1,B)
(¬zB V l2,B)

(¬zC V ¬s1,C)
(¬zC V ¬s2,C)
(¬zC V l1,C)
(¬zC V ¬l2,C)
(¬zC V ¬l1,C)
(¬zC V l2,C)

EXEMPLO COM UMA CLAUSULA (RESTRIÇÃO 5)

c1
(z1 V zA1 V zB1 V zC1)

(¬z1 V c1)

(¬zA1 V ¬s1,A)
(¬zA1 V ¬l1,A)

(¬zB1 V ¬s1,B)
(¬zB1 V ¬l1,B)

(¬zC1 V ¬s1,C)
(¬zC1 V ¬l1,C)

EXEMPLO COM TRÊS CLAUSULAS (RESTRIÇÃO 5)

c1 <-> c2
(z1 V zA1 V zB1 V zC1)

(¬z1 V ¬c1 V c2)
(¬z1 V c1 V ¬c2)

(¬zA1 V ¬s1,A)
(¬zA1 V ¬s2,A)
(¬zA1 V l1,A)
(¬zA1 V ¬l2,A)
(¬zA1 V ¬l1,A)
(¬zA1 V l2,A)

